Added git-pull-other for pulling specific refs from default remote.

Created utility script to fetch and update a local reference from the default
remote without checking out the branch.

Features:
- Takes a <local-ref> argument specifying which ref to update
- Uses git config checkout.defaultRemote (falls back to first remote)
- Supports --verbose and --quiet flags for output control
- Uses git rev-parse --parseopt for proper help/option handling
- Validates the local reference exists before attempting fetch

This allows updating local branches from remote without checking them out,
useful for keeping multiple branches synchronized with minimal switching.

